### Test Rooms API Endpoints
### Make sure your backend is running on localhost:3000

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@token = YOUR_AUTH_TOKEN_HERE

### 1. Get all rooms
GET {{baseUrl}}/rooms
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2. Create a new room
POST {{baseUrl}}/rooms
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomNumber": "101",
  "capacity": 2,
  "type": "consultation",
  "isAvailable": true
}

### 3. Get room by ID (replace with actual ID from create response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/rooms/YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 4. Update room
PUT {{baseUrl}}/rooms/YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "roomNumber": "101A",
  "capacity": 3,
  "type": "consultation",
  "isAvailable": true
}

### 5. Get available rooms
GET {{baseUrl}}/rooms/available
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Update room availability
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/rooms/YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE/availability
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "isAvailable": false
}

### 7. Delete room
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/rooms/YOUR_ROOM_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
